        "title":"Greece joins Picasso power balancing platform",
        "subtitle":"\n              (Montel) Greece joined the\u00a0EU\u2019s cross-border power balancing mechanism\u00a0Picasso on 18 March, power grid operator confirmed to Montel on Thursday.\n            ",
        "body":"\nThe start date is in line with a statement made by Greek TSO Ipto on 12 February.\nNevertheless, the development came as a surprise to some market participants, with one trader telling Montel that they had expected it to happen in June.\nGreece is the second country in southeast Europe to join Picasso, after Bulgaria implemented the mechanism last month.\u00a0\nGreece\u2019s entry could encourage other major regional markets \u2013 such as Romania and even Hungary \u2013 to expedite their joining.\nThe\u00a0Picasso\u00a0platform was launched in 2022 with the aim of supporting balancing markets by sharing capacity between European countries. A number of countries delayed their entry last year, amid concerns the algorithm caused price spikes.\n",
